questions.quote: Hi Emma! It's the year 2020. Are you still enjoying your nap?
Damn it woman, pull yourself together! Have some pride, for the love of God.
No! Of course we can still hang out with them. Just y'know, not two nights in a row. Okay?
Because she's not eleven! And it's not the seventh night of Hanukkah!
All right, now you know that the ATM will only lets you take out 300 at a time, I'll take a check for the other hundred.
Well, I don't care! That-that turkey has to feed 20 people at my parent's house and they're not gonna eat it off your head!
No-no, no! We have to move the table into my room, yeah! 'Cause of all the boxes. Come on!
All right. So you're telling me that there is nothing going on between you and Chandler.
Sweetie, it's be gonna okay, all right. It's a wedding, generally people focus on the bride.
Look, face it, my father is not going to pay for the build-in barbecue and believe me you can kiss you gazebo goodbye. Now I might be able to get you the new lawn.
